  "steps": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "instruction": "In the bowl of your crockpot, combine the chicken, onion, garlic, brown sugar (or honey), chipotle chile peppers, paprika, oregano, cumin, cinnamon, salt, salsa and diced green chiles. Add 1/2 cup water, cover and cook on LOW for 6-7 hours or on HIGH for 4-6 hours. Once the chicken is done cooking, shred with two forks and then stir in the lime juice and cilantro."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "instruction": "Serve the chicken in warmed taco boats, tortillas or use in wraps. Top as desired."
    }
